videos.description: Jordan Ta'amu delivers a nice pass to A.J. Brown who takes it down the sideline and dives into the end zone for a touchdown.
videos.headline: Ta'amu throws perfect pass to Brown for Ole Miss TD

videos.description: Keith Ford battles through Ole Miss defenders and scores a touchdown to tie the game 7-7.
videos.headline: Ford punches it in on 3rd down for an Aggies TD

videos.description: Jordan Wilkins runs 64 yards to the house for a touchdown to give the Rebels' back the lead 14-7 in the first quarter.
videos.headline: Ole Miss' Wilkins shows off speed with 64-yard rushing TD

videos.description: Nick Starkel finds Damion Ratley in the end zone for a 10-yard touchdown pass to tie the game 14-14.
videos.headline: Texas A&M answers with 10 yard TD

videos.description: Nick Starkel's pass is intercepted by Ole Miss' Myles Hartsfield to give the Rebels back the ball.
videos.headline: Starkel picked off by Ole Miss defense

videos.description: Jordan Ta'amu  finds wide-open Braylon Sanders for 30 yard touchdown to give the Rebels the lead 21-14 in the second quarter.
videos.headline: Ta'amu strikes again for an Ole Miss TD

videos.description: Nick Starkel keeps the football and punches it in for an Aggies touchdown to tie the game 21-21.
videos.headline: Texas A&M's Starkel responds with short rushing TD

videos.description: Zaycoven Henderson is ejected for the remainder of the game after a hard late hit to Ole Miss QB Jordan Ta'amu.
videos.headline: Texas A&M's Henderson ejected for targeting

videos.description: Ole Miss interim coach Matt Luke says his offense had a lot of great opportunities in the first half of the game against Texas A&M.
videos.headline: Luke wants team to stay balanced in second half

videos.description: Jodan Ta'amu pass is intercepted by Derrick Tucker who returns it for a touchdown to put the Aggies ahead 28-24.
videos.headline: Texas A&M's Tucker returns interception for 19 yard TD

videos.description: Tommy Tuberville and Mike Patrick discuss the offensive plays of both teams in the first half. They credit Texas A&M's defense in the second half for leading the Aggies to a 31-24 victory against Ole Miss.
videos.headline: Tuberville: 'First half was all offense'
